                <h1>Understanding NICS: Protecting Communities Through Responsible Gun Sales</h1>
                <p>NICS, or the National Instant Criminal Background Check System, is a crucial tool in maintaining public safety by preventing firearm sales to prohibited individuals. Established in 1998, the system allows federal firearms licensees to check a buyer's background in real-time, ensuring compliance with federal regulations and enhancing responsible gun ownership.</p>
